{"id": "faith_001", "prompt": "Based on the following policy document, what are the eligibility requirements for a home equity line of credit?", "context": "HOME EQUITY LINE OF CREDIT POLICY: Eligibility requires: (1) minimum credit score of 680, (2) maximum combined loan-to-value ratio of 85%, (3) property must be primary residence, (4) minimum 2 years of employment history. Maximum line amount: $500,000. Draw period: 10 years. Repayment period: 20 years.", "reference": "Credit score >= 680, CLTV <= 85%, primary residence, 2+ years employment", "metadata": {"category": "rag_policy", "source": "heloc_policy_v3"}}
{"id": "faith_002", "prompt": "According to the customer's account summary, what products do they currently hold?", "context": "ACCOUNT SUMMARY - Customer: John Smith (ID: 847291). Products: (1) Premier Checking - Balance: $12,450.33, (2) High-Yield Savings - Balance: $45,200.00, APY: 4.25%, (3) 12-month CD - Principal: $25,000, Rate: 4.75%, Maturity: 08/15/2024. No active loans or credit cards on file.", "reference": "Premier Checking, High-Yield Savings, 12-month CD. No loans or credit cards.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_customer_data"}}
{"id": "faith_003", "prompt": "What is the maximum transfer limit for online banking according to this policy?", "context": "ONLINE BANKING TRANSFER POLICY (Rev. 2024-03): Internal transfers between owned accounts: No daily limit. External transfers to other institutions: $10,000 per day, $25,000 per month. Wire transfers: $50,000 per day for personal accounts, $250,000 for business accounts. All limits may be increased by visiting a branch with valid ID. Transfers initiated after 5:00 PM ET are processed the next business day.", "reference": "Internal: no limit. External: $10,000/day, $25,000/month. Wire: $50,000/day personal, $250,000/day business.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_policy", "source": "online_banking_policy"}}
{"id": "faith_004", "prompt": "What fees apply to this checking account?", "context": "PREMIER CHECKING ACCOUNT SCHEDULE OF FEES: Monthly maintenance fee: $25 (waived with $15,000 combined balance or $5,000 in direct deposits). ATM fees: No fee at network ATMs; $3.00 per non-network ATM transaction (domestic); $5.00 per international ATM transaction. Overdraft fee: $35 per occurrence, maximum 3 per day ($105 cap). Wire transfer (outgoing domestic): $30. Wire transfer (outgoing international): $50. Wire transfer (incoming): No fee. Stop payment: $35. Cashier's check: No fee. Account research: $25 per hour (minimum 1 hour).", "reference": "Monthly maintenance $25 (waivable), ATM $3-5 non-network, overdraft $35 (max 3/day), domestic wire $30, international wire $50, stop payment $35", "metadata": {"category": "rag_fee_schedule"}}
{"id": "faith_005", "prompt": "Based on this compliance memo, what changes are being made to the BSA program?", "context": "COMPLIANCE MEMO 2024-017: Effective April 1, 2024, the following changes to our BSA/AML program take effect: (1) Enhanced Due Diligence (EDD) threshold for high-risk customers lowered from $1M to $500K in aggregate deposits. (2) SAR filing review period shortened from 60 to 45 calendar days. (3) New automated transaction monitoring rules for cryptocurrency-related activity. (4) Annual BSA training requirement increased from 2 hours to 4 hours for all customer-facing staff. (5) Beneficial ownership re-verification required every 2 years instead of 3 years. Contact BSA Officer Maria Chen (ext. 4521) with questions.", "reference": "EDD threshold lowered to $500K, SAR review shortened to 45 days, new crypto monitoring rules, training increased to 4 hours, beneficial ownership re-verification every 2 years", "metadata": {"category": "rag_compliance_memo"}}
{"id": "faith_006", "prompt": "What does this customer's credit report indicate about their payment history?", "context": "CREDIT REPORT SUMMARY - Applicant: Sarah Johnson. FICO Score: 742. Payment History: 99% on-time payments over 15-year credit history. One 30-day late payment on auto loan (March 2022) due to payment processing error, subsequently corrected. Total accounts: 8 (5 open, 3 closed in good standing). Credit utilization: 23% across all revolving accounts. Average account age: 8.4 years. Recent inquiries: 2 in last 6 months (mortgage pre-approval). Collections: None. Public records: None.", "reference": "99% on-time, one 30-day late in March 2022 (processing error, corrected), 23% utilization, no collections or public records, FICO 742", "metadata": {"category": "rag_credit_report"}}
{"id": "faith_007", "prompt": "What are the terms of this CD product?", "context": "CERTIFICATE OF DEPOSIT PRODUCT SHEET - 13-Month CD Special: APY: 5.10%. Minimum deposit: $1,000. Maximum deposit: $1,000,000. Term: 13 months. Early withdrawal penalty: 90 days of interest. Interest payment options: Monthly to linked account, or compounded and paid at maturity. Renewal: Automatically renews at the standard 12-month CD rate unless customer provides instructions within 10-day grace period. FDIC insured up to applicable limits. Available for individual, joint, trust, and IRA accounts.", "reference": "13-month term, 5.10% APY, $1,000 min, $1M max, 90-day interest penalty for early withdrawal, auto-renews at 12-month rate", "metadata": {"category": "rag_product_sheet"}}
{"id": "faith_008", "prompt": "According to this audit finding, what deficiencies were identified?", "context": "INTERNAL AUDIT REPORT 2024-Q1 - Branch Operations Review, Downtown Branch: Finding 1 (HIGH): Cash drawer overages/shortages exceeded $50 threshold on 7 occasions during Q1. Root cause: Inconsistent dual-count procedures. Finding 2 (MEDIUM): 12 of 45 new account files (27%) were missing signed Patriot Act disclosure forms. Finding 3 (LOW): Vault access log showed 3 instances of single-person vault entry without required dual control. Remediation deadline: All findings must be addressed within 30 days. Branch Manager acknowledgment required by March 31, 2024.", "reference": "Three findings: cash drawer discrepancies (HIGH), missing Patriot Act disclosures in 27% of files (MEDIUM), vault dual control violations (LOW). 30-day remediation required.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_audit_report"}}
{"id": "faith_009", "prompt": "What investment options are available in this 401(k) plan according to the summary?", "context": "401(K) PLAN INVESTMENT OPTIONS SUMMARY - Employer: Meridian Financial Group. Plan Administrator: Fidelity Investments. Available Funds: (1) Fidelity 500 Index Fund (FXAIX) - ER 0.015%, (2) Fidelity Total Bond Index (FXNAX) - ER 0.025%, (3) Fidelity International Index (FSPSX) - ER 0.035%, (4) Fidelity Small Cap Index (FSSNX) - ER 0.025%, (5) Fidelity Government Money Market (SPAXX) - ER 0.42%, (6) Target Date Funds 2025-2065 (5-year increments) - ER 0.12%. Company match: 100% of first 3%, 50% of next 2%. Vesting: 3-year cliff vesting for employer contributions.", "reference": "Six fund categories including S&P 500 index, total bond, international, small cap, money market, and target date funds. Company match is 100% on first 3%, 50% on next 2%. 3-year cliff vesting.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_plan_summary"}}
{"id": "faith_010", "prompt": "Based on this rate sheet, what mortgage rates are currently offered?", "context": "MORTGAGE RATE SHEET - Effective Date: March 15, 2024. 30-Year Fixed: 6.875% rate / 6.950% APR (0 points). 30-Year Fixed: 6.625% rate / 6.825% APR (1 point). 15-Year Fixed: 6.250% rate / 6.350% APR (0 points). 5/1 ARM: 5.750% rate / 7.150% APR (0 points). 7/1 ARM: 6.125% rate / 7.050% APR (0 points). FHA 30-Year: 6.500% rate / 7.250% APR (includes MIP). VA 30-Year: 6.250% rate / 6.500% APR. Jumbo 30-Year Fixed: 7.125% rate / 7.200% APR. Rates subject to change without notice. All rates assume 740+ FICO and 80% LTV.", "reference": "30yr fixed 6.875%, 15yr fixed 6.250%, 5/1 ARM 5.750%, FHA 6.500%, VA 6.250%, Jumbo 7.125%. Rates assume 740+ FICO, 80% LTV.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_rate_sheet"}}
{"id": "faith_011", "prompt": "What dispute resolution process does the customer agreement describe?", "context": "DEPOSIT ACCOUNT AGREEMENT - Section 14: Dispute Resolution. 14.1 Informal Resolution: Customer must first contact Customer Service at 1-800-555-0123 or visit a branch to attempt informal resolution. 14.2 Written Complaint: If unresolved within 15 business days, customer may submit a written complaint to Complaint Resolution Department, PO Box 12345, Dallas TX 75001. Bank will respond within 30 business days. 14.3 Mediation: Either party may request non-binding mediation through AAA (American Arbitration Association). Costs shared equally. 14.4 Arbitration: If mediation fails, disputes will be resolved by binding arbitration under AAA Commercial Rules. Class action waiver applies. 14.5 Regulatory Complaints: Customer retains right to file complaints with CFPB, OCC, or state banking regulators at any time.", "reference": "Four-step process: informal resolution via phone/branch, written complaint (30-day response), AAA mediation (shared cost), binding arbitration with class action waiver. Can always file with CFPB/OCC.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_account_agreement"}}
{"id": "faith_012", "prompt": "What does this training manual say about identifying elder financial exploitation?", "context": "EMPLOYEE TRAINING MANUAL - Chapter 9: Elder Financial Exploitation. Red Flags: (1) Sudden changes in banking patterns or account activity. (2) Unexplained withdrawals or transfers to unfamiliar parties. (3) New authorized signers or POA additions. (4) Customer appears confused, fearful, or accompanied by controlling individual. (5) Sudden changes to beneficiary designations or estate documents. (6) Customer unable to explain transactions on their account. Required Actions: Report suspected exploitation to Branch Manager immediately. File SAR if suspicious activity threshold met. Contact Adult Protective Services if immediate harm suspected. Document all observations in CRM case notes. Do NOT confront the suspected abuser.", "reference": "Six red flags including sudden banking changes, unexplained withdrawals, new signers, confused/fearful customer, beneficiary changes, inability to explain transactions. Must report to manager, file SAR if warranted, contact APS if immediate harm, document in CRM, do not confront abuser.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_training_manual"}}
{"id": "faith_013", "prompt": "According to this loan approval memo, what conditions must be met before closing?", "context": "LOAN APPROVAL MEMO - Borrower: Michael & Karen Torres. Loan Type: Conventional 30-Year Fixed. Amount: $425,000. Rate: 6.75%. LTV: 78%. Approval Status: APPROVED WITH CONDITIONS. Conditions Prior to Closing: (1) Provide most recent 30 days of pay stubs (both borrowers). (2) Written explanation and documentation for $15,000 deposit on 02/14/2024 statement. (3) Termite inspection clearance. (4) Title insurance commitment with no exceptions other than standard. (5) Flood certification - property must not be in SFHA. (6) Homeowner's insurance binder naming bank as mortgagee. Approval expires: 60 days from date of this memo (May 15, 2024).", "reference": "Six conditions: recent pay stubs, explanation of $15K deposit, termite clearance, clean title commitment, flood certification, insurance binder. Approval expires May 15, 2024.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_loan_approval"}}
{"id": "faith_014", "prompt": "What does this wire transfer policy say about international wires?", "context": "WIRE TRANSFER POLICY (Internal Use Only): International Outgoing Wires: Must be initiated in branch with valid government-issued photo ID. Beneficiary bank must have valid SWIFT code. Maximum $100,000 per day for personal accounts without manager override. Enhanced due diligence required for: (a) transfers to FATF high-risk jurisdictions, (b) first-time international wire recipients, (c) any wire over $50,000. All international wires are screened against OFAC SDN list before processing. Cut-off time: 2:00 PM ET for same-day processing. Fee: $50 outgoing, $15 incoming. Intermediary bank fees may apply and are not disclosed in advance. Currency conversion uses bank's posted exchange rate at time of processing plus 1.5% markup.", "reference": "In-branch only with photo ID. Max $100K/day personal. Enhanced due diligence for high-risk countries, first-time recipients, over $50K. OFAC screened. Cut-off 2PM ET. Fee $50 out/$15 in. 1.5% FX markup.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_wire_policy"}}
{"id": "faith_015", "prompt": "Based on this customer's transaction history, summarize their recent activity.", "context": "TRANSACTION HISTORY - Account: Premier Checking ****4521. Period: March 1-15, 2024.\n03/01 Direct Deposit - Employer Payroll: +$4,250.00 (Bal: $8,732.45)\n03/02 Debit Card - Whole Foods #1042: -$187.34 (Bal: $8,545.11)\n03/03 Online Transfer to Savings: -$1,500.00 (Bal: $7,045.11)\n03/05 ACH - Mortgage Payment: -$2,528.00 (Bal: $4,517.11)\n03/05 ACH - Auto Insurance: -$156.00 (Bal: $4,361.11)\n03/07 Debit Card - Shell Gas Station: -$62.50 (Bal: $4,298.61)\n03/08 Zelle Received - From M. Torres: +$500.00 (Bal: $4,798.61)\n03/10 Check #1847 - Dr. Anderson: -$250.00 (Bal: $4,548.61)\n03/12 Debit Card - Amazon.com: -$89.99 (Bal: $4,458.62)\n03/14 ACH - Electric Utility: -$143.00 (Bal: $4,315.62)\n03/15 Direct Deposit - Employer Payroll: +$4,250.00 (Bal: $8,565.62)", "reference": "Two payroll deposits of $4,250 each. Major expenses: mortgage $2,528, savings transfer $1,500, groceries $187, auto insurance $156, utilities $143. One incoming Zelle $500. Current balance $8,565.62.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_transaction_history"}}
{"id": "faith_016", "prompt": "What does this regulation summary say about flood insurance requirements?", "context": "REGULATORY SUMMARY - Flood Insurance (NFIA/Biggert-Waters Act): Lenders must require flood insurance on any property located in a Special Flood Hazard Area (SFHA) as designated by FEMA. Minimum coverage: lesser of outstanding loan balance or maximum available under NFIP ($250,000 for residential structures, $500,000 for commercial). Force-placed insurance: If borrower fails to maintain coverage, lender must force-place insurance within 45 days of notification and may charge the cost to the borrower. Private flood insurance: Acceptable if it meets the statutory definition under Biggert-Waters Section 102(b). SFHA determination must be made using current FEMA flood maps. Determination must be retained for the life of the loan.", "reference": "Flood insurance required for SFHA properties. Coverage minimum is lesser of loan balance or NFIP max ($250K residential, $500K commercial). Force-place within 45 days if lapsed. Private flood OK if meets statutory definition. FEMA map determination kept for life of loan.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_regulatory_summary"}}
{"id": "faith_017", "prompt": "What are the key terms of this business line of credit?", "context": "BUSINESS LINE OF CREDIT - TERM SHEET. Borrower: Apex Manufacturing LLC. Facility: Revolving Line of Credit. Commitment Amount: $750,000. Interest Rate: Prime + 1.50% (currently 9.50%), variable, adjusted monthly. Unused Line Fee: 0.25% annually on unused portion. Draw Period: 24 months. Repayment: Interest-only during draw period; 36-month amortization of outstanding balance at end of draw period. Collateral: First lien on all business assets (UCC-1 filing). Guaranty: Personal guaranty of majority owner (Thomas Reed, 60% ownership). Financial Covenants: (1) Debt service coverage ratio minimum 1.25x, (2) Current ratio minimum 1.50x, (3) Annual audited financials due within 120 days of fiscal year end. Origination Fee: 1.00% ($7,500). Documentation Fee: $500.", "reference": "$750K revolving line at Prime+1.50% (9.50%), 24-month draw with interest-only, then 36-month amortization. Secured by all business assets. Personal guaranty from majority owner. Covenants: 1.25x DSCR, 1.50x current ratio. 1% origination fee.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_term_sheet"}}
{"id": "faith_018", "prompt": "What does this compliance alert say about the new beneficial ownership reporting requirements?", "context": "COMPLIANCE ALERT 2024-003: Corporate Transparency Act (CTA) Implementation. Effective January 1, 2024, most companies must file Beneficial Ownership Information (BOI) reports with FinCEN. Key Points: (1) Existing companies formed before 1/1/2024 have until 1/1/2025 to file. (2) New companies formed in 2024 must file within 90 days of formation. (3) Companies formed in 2025 or later must file within 30 days. (4) Reports must identify all beneficial owners with 25%+ ownership or substantial control. (5) Required information: legal name, date of birth, address, and government ID number for each beneficial owner. (6) 23 categories of exempt entities including publicly traded companies, banks, and large operating companies (20+ FT employees, $5M+ revenue, US physical presence). (7) Updates must be filed within 30 days of any change. NOTE: This is a FinCEN filing requirement, NOT a bank CDD requirement, but banks should be aware of it for customer conversations.", "reference": "CTA requires BOI reports to FinCEN. Existing companies file by 1/1/2025, new 2024 companies within 90 days, 2025+ within 30 days. Must report 25%+ owners or controllers with name, DOB, address, ID. 23 exempt categories. Updates within 30 days. Separate from bank CDD.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_compliance_alert"}}
{"id": "faith_019", "prompt": "According to this performance review, how is the branch performing?", "context": "QUARTERLY BRANCH PERFORMANCE REPORT - Q1 2024, Westside Branch. New Accounts: 142 (target: 125, 114% of goal). Deposit Growth: +$4.2M (+3.8% QoQ, target: +3.0%). Loan Origination: $12.1M (target: $15M, 81% of goal). Cross-Sell Ratio: 3.2 products per household (target: 3.5). Customer Satisfaction (NPS): 72 (target: 65). Employee Turnover: 8% annualized (target: <15%). Compliance: 0 regulatory findings. Areas of Concern: Loan origination 19% below target due to rate environment. Action Items: (1) Increase mortgage refinance outreach. (2) Promote HELOC product to existing customers. (3) Schedule 2 community lending events in Q2. Branch Manager Rating: MEETS EXPECTATIONS.", "reference": "Strong new accounts (114% of goal) and deposits (+3.8% vs 3.0% target). Loan origination missed at 81% of goal. NPS 72 exceeds target of 65. Zero compliance findings. Rating: meets expectations.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_performance_report"}}
{"id": "faith_020", "prompt": "What does this complaint record show about the customer's issue?", "context": "COMPLAINT RECORD #CR-2024-0847. Customer: Angela White. Account: Savings ****9012. Date Filed: March 3, 2024. Channel: Phone (call recorded). Complaint Summary: Customer reports being charged $35 overdraft fee on checking account on 2/28/2024, but states she had sufficient funds when the transaction was initiated. Transaction: Debit card purchase at Target for $127.50. Account balance at time of swipe: $152.33. Pending transactions at time of posting: ACH payment to utility ($89.00) posted before debit card transaction, reducing available balance to $63.33. Investigation: Transaction reordering compliant with posted account agreement terms. However, customer was not opted in to overdraft coverage for debit card transactions per Reg E. Resolution: Overdraft fee reversed ($35 credit applied 3/5/2024). Training reminder sent to debit card operations team regarding Reg E opt-in requirements. Status: RESOLVED - Customer satisfied.", "reference": "Customer charged $35 overdraft fee despite sufficient balance at swipe time. ACH posted first reducing balance. Fee reversed because customer was not opted in to overdraft coverage per Reg E. Resolved with refund and staff training reminder.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_complaint_record"}}
{"id": "faith_021", "prompt": "Based on this CRA exam summary, how did the bank perform?", "context": "CRA PERFORMANCE EVALUATION SUMMARY - First National Community Bank. Evaluation Period: January 2021 - December 2023. Overall Rating: SATISFACTORY. Lending Test: HIGH SATISFACTORY. Distribution of loans reflects good penetration among borrowers of different income levels. Geographic distribution shows good penetration in LMI census tracts. Investment Test: LOW SATISFACTORY. Qualified investments totaled $2.3M (0.8% of Tier 1 capital). Primarily mortgage-backed securities; limited community development investments. Service Test: HIGH SATISFACTORY. Branch distribution provides good accessibility to LMI areas. 3 of 12 branches located in LMI tracts. No branch closings in LMI areas during evaluation period. Free checking account product available.", "reference": "Overall Satisfactory. Lending test: high satisfactory with good penetration in LMI areas. Investment test: low satisfactory at $2.3M (0.8% Tier 1), limited CD investments. Service test: high satisfactory, 3/12 branches in LMI tracts, no LMI branch closings.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_regulatory_exam"}}
{"id": "faith_022", "prompt": "What does the employee handbook say about gifts and entertainment from vendors?", "context": "EMPLOYEE HANDBOOK - Section 7.3: Gifts and Entertainment Policy. Employees may accept: (1) Gifts of nominal value (under $50) if customary business courtesy. (2) Business meals with vendors if discussion of legitimate business matters occurs. (3) Promotional items of minimal value (pens, calendars, etc.). Employees may NOT accept: (1) Cash or cash equivalents (gift cards) of any amount. (2) Gifts exceeding $50 in value without written pre-approval from Compliance. (3) Travel, lodging, or event tickets unless pre-approved. (4) Any gift from a customer or applicant with a pending loan application. (5) Gifts that could create a conflict of interest or appearance of impropriety. All gifts over $25 must be reported to the Gift and Entertainment Log within 5 business days. Violations may result in disciplinary action up to and including termination.", "reference": "Under $50 gifts OK if customary. Business meals OK. No cash/gift cards ever. Over $50 requires Compliance approval. No gifts from pending loan applicants. All gifts over $25 must be logged within 5 business days.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_employee_handbook"}}
{"id": "faith_023", "prompt": "What trust services does this brochure describe?", "context": "WEALTH MANAGEMENT TRUST SERVICES BROCHURE. Services Offered: (1) Revocable Living Trusts - Asset management, bill payment, investment oversight during grantor's lifetime. Annual fee: 0.75% of trust assets (minimum $5,000). (2) Irrevocable Trusts - ILIT, GRAT, QPRT management. Annual fee: 1.00% of trust assets (minimum $7,500). (3) Testamentary Trust Administration - Post-death trust funding and administration per will terms. Fee: 1.25% of assets. (4) Special Needs Trusts - Government benefit preservation, discretionary distributions. Fee: 1.00% (minimum $4,000). (5) Charitable Remainder Trusts - CRT administration and annual tax reporting. Fee: 0.85% of assets. All fees are subject to negotiation based on asset level and complexity. Minimum trust size: $500,000 for most trust types ($250,000 for Special Needs). Trust officer assigned to each account. Quarterly performance reports and annual in-person reviews included.", "reference": "Five trust types: revocable (0.75%), irrevocable (1.00%), testamentary (1.25%), special needs (1.00%), charitable remainder (0.85%). Minimum $500K for most types, $250K for special needs. Assigned trust officer, quarterly reports, annual reviews.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_product_brochure"}}
{"id": "faith_024", "prompt": "What does this IT security policy require for online banking access?", "context": "IT SECURITY POLICY - Section 4: Online Banking Authentication. Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) is required for: all login attempts, high-risk transactions (external transfers, wire transfers, payee additions, profile changes). MFA Methods: (1) SMS one-time passcode (default), (2) Authentication app (Google Authenticator, Microsoft Authenticator), (3) Hardware security key (FIDO2/WebAuthn). Session Management: Sessions expire after 15 minutes of inactivity. Maximum session duration: 4 hours. Failed Login: Account locked after 5 consecutive failed attempts. Unlock via: (a) automated phone verification, (b) branch visit with ID, (c) customer service call with identity verification. Password Requirements: Minimum 12 characters, must include uppercase, lowercase, number, and special character. No reuse of last 12 passwords. Password change required every 90 days.", "reference": "MFA required for all logins and high-risk transactions. Three MFA options: SMS, authenticator app, hardware key. 15-minute inactivity timeout. Lock after 5 failed attempts. Passwords: 12+ chars, complexity required, change every 90 days.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_security_policy"}}
{"id": "faith_025", "prompt": "What are the key findings from this market analysis report?", "context": "MARKET ANALYSIS REPORT - Retail Banking Trends Q1 2024. Key Findings: (1) Deposit competition remains intense; average savings APY across top-20 banks rose to 4.35% from 3.90% year-over-year. (2) CD rates peaked in Q4 2023 and are trending down slightly; 12-month CD average now 4.85% vs. 5.10% peak. (3) Mortgage origination volumes down 22% YoY due to sustained high rates; refinance activity at historic lows. (4) Digital banking adoption: 78% of customers now use mobile banking weekly (up from 71% in 2023). (5) Branch traffic continues to decline (-8% YoY) but in-branch revenue per visit up 15% as routine transactions move digital. (6) Net interest margin compression: average NIM for community banks fell to 3.15% from 3.45% in Q1 2023. Recommendations: Focus on relationship deepening, digital experience, and fee-based services to offset NIM pressure.", "reference": "Savings rates up to 4.35%, CD rates slightly declining from 5.10% peak. Mortgage originations down 22%. Mobile banking at 78% weekly usage. Branch traffic down 8% but revenue per visit up 15%. Community bank NIM compressed to 3.15%.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_market_analysis"}}
{"id": "faith_026", "prompt": "What does this SBA loan program guide explain about 7(a) loans?", "context": "SBA LOAN PROGRAM GUIDE - 7(a) Loan Program: Maximum loan amount: $5,000,000. Eligible uses: Working capital, equipment, real estate, business acquisition, refinancing. Guaranty: SBA guarantees up to 85% of loans $150,000 or less, and 75% of loans over $150,000. Interest Rates: Negotiated between borrower and lender, subject to SBA maximums. Variable rate loans: Prime + 2.25% to Prime + 4.75% depending on loan size and maturity. Fixed rate loans available for terms over 15 years. Maturity: Up to 10 years for working capital, 25 years for real estate. Fees: Guaranty fee ranges from 2% to 3.75% based on loan amount and maturity. Collateral: Required for loans over $25,000; SBA will not decline solely for lack of collateral. Eligibility: For-profit business, operates in US, owner has invested equity, exhausted other financing options.", "reference": "Max $5M. 85% guarantee up to $150K, 75% above. Variable rates Prime+2.25%-4.75%. Up to 10yr working capital, 25yr real estate. Guaranty fee 2%-3.75%. Collateral required over $25K but not sole decline factor.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_program_guide"}}
{"id": "faith_027", "prompt": "Based on this incident report, what happened and what actions were taken?", "context": "SECURITY INCIDENT REPORT #IR-2024-0192. Date: March 8, 2024. Type: Attempted Social Engineering. Summary: At approximately 2:15 PM, a caller contacted the Private Banking team claiming to be Robert Chen (account holder ****7834). Caller requested a $95,000 wire transfer to an account at Banco Nacional de Mexico. Red flags identified: (1) Caller ID showed international number, not customer's known numbers. (2) Caller could not verify mother's maiden name. (3) Transaction type and destination inconsistent with customer's history. Actions Taken: (1) Transfer request denied. (2) Account flagged for enhanced monitoring. (3) Actual customer contacted at known phone number and confirmed no wire was requested. (4) SAR filed (SAR #2024-0847). (5) Caller's number added to internal fraud database. (6) Incident escalated to BSA Officer and Information Security. Status: CLOSED. Customer account secured with temporary hold requiring in-branch verification for all wire requests.", "reference": "Attempted social engineering via phone for $95K international wire. Denied due to wrong caller ID, failed security question, unusual transaction pattern. Real customer confirmed no request. SAR filed. Account secured with in-branch wire requirement.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_incident_report"}}
{"id": "faith_028", "prompt": "What does this board resolution authorize?", "context": "BOARD OF DIRECTORS RESOLUTION #2024-012. Date: February 28, 2024. Subject: Authorization of New Branch Location. RESOLVED, that the Board of Directors of First Community Bancorp hereby authorizes: (1) The opening of a de novo branch at 2847 Innovation Drive, Suite 100, Austin, TX 78746. (2) Capital expenditure not to exceed $2.8 million for build-out, furnishing, and technology infrastructure. (3) Initial staffing of 8 FTE positions (1 Branch Manager, 1 Assistant Manager, 3 Personal Bankers, 2 Tellers, 1 Operations Specialist). (4) Filing of all required regulatory applications with the OCC and Texas Department of Banking. (5) Appointment of SVP Lisa Martinez as Project Lead. (6) Target opening date: Q3 2024. FURTHER RESOLVED, that the CEO is authorized to execute all documents necessary to effectuate this resolution. Vote: 9-0 (unanimous). Abstentions: None.", "reference": "Unanimously authorized new branch at 2847 Innovation Drive, Austin TX. Budget up to $2.8M. 8 FTE staff. OCC and state regulatory applications to be filed. Lisa Martinez as project lead. Target Q3 2024 opening.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_board_resolution"}}
{"id": "faith_029", "prompt": "What risk factors does this commercial loan analysis identify?", "context": "COMMERCIAL CREDIT ANALYSIS - Borrower: Pacific Coast Hospitality Group. Industry: Hotel/Hospitality. Request: $3.2M term loan for property renovation. Risk Assessment: MODERATE. Positive Factors: (1) 15-year operating history with stable revenue. (2) Current DSCR of 1.85x exceeds policy minimum of 1.25x. (3) Experienced management team. (4) Property appraised at $5.8M (LTV: 55%). Negative Factors: (1) Hospitality industry cyclicality and sensitivity to economic downturns. (2) Revenue concentration: 40% from single corporate client contract expiring in 18 months. (3) Deferred maintenance estimated at $450K beyond renovation scope. (4) Local market showing 12% increase in hotel supply over next 2 years. Mitigants: Client has letter of intent for contract renewal. Cash reserves of $800K. Personal guaranty of 100% owner with $2.1M net worth outside business.", "reference": "Moderate risk. Positives: 15yr history, 1.85x DSCR, 55% LTV. Negatives: cyclical industry, 40% revenue concentration from one contract expiring in 18 months, $450K deferred maintenance, increasing local supply. Mitigated by contract renewal LOI, $800K reserves, strong personal guaranty.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_credit_analysis"}}
{"id": "faith_030", "prompt": "What retirement plan changes are described in this HR memo?", "context": "HR MEMORANDUM - To: All Employees. Subject: 2024 Retirement Plan Enhancements. Effective April 1, 2024: (1) Employer match increased from 4% to 5% of eligible compensation. (2) Immediate vesting for employer contributions (previously 3-year cliff). (3) Student loan repayment matching: Employees making qualified student loan payments are now eligible for employer matching contributions to their 401(k) under SECURE 2.0 provisions. Amount: $0.50 per $1 of qualified student loan payment, up to 5% of compensation. (4) Roth 401(k) option now available for all participants. (5) Auto-enrollment for new hires at 6% deferral rate (up from 3%), with 1% annual auto-escalation up to 15%. (6) Emergency savings account: New after-tax account linked to 401(k); up to $2,500 with one fee-free withdrawal per month. Questions: Contact HR Benefits team at benefits@firstcommunity.com.", "reference": "Six changes: match increased to 5%, immediate vesting, student loan repayment matching ($0.50/$1 up to 5%), Roth option added, auto-enrollment increased to 6% with 1% escalation, emergency savings account up to $2,500. Effective April 1, 2024.", "metadata": {"category": "rag_hr_memo"}}
